      <bioghist>
         
         
         <head>Biographical Note</head>
         
         
         <p>Hinson was a Methodist minister who spent most of
		  his career pastoring churches in North Carolina.</p>
      
      
      </bioghist><!--End of biohistory--><!--Begin scopecontent-->
      
      
      <scopecontent>
         
         
         <head>Collection Overview</head>
         
         
         <p>The collection documenting the life and religious
		  writings of O.I. Hinson consists of 45 handwritten 
		  sermons and outlines of
		  sermons by Hinson, [ca. 1914]-1932; 20 letters written
		  between 1937-1939 and 1946-1947, from Hinson to his
		  brother, Jeremias Enos Hinson; a 
		  photograph of Hinson; and a
		  small number of 
		  clippings and other
		  miscellaneous papers.</p>
      
      
      </scopecontent><!--End scopecontent--><!--Begin controlaccess-->
      
      
